This product uses the ANTLR 4 runtime library (org.antlr:antlr4-runtime)
as a runtime dependency for parsing C# source files. The ANTLR 4 grammar
tool (org.antlr:antlr4) is used only at build time to generate the parser
from the CSharpTest.g4 grammar and is not distributed with this product.

The CSharpTest.g4 grammar was written independently for this project,
based on the C# language specification (ECMA-334). It was verified not to
be derived from the antlr/grammars-v4 C# grammars (which carry an EPL-1.0
+ MIT dual license incompatible with Apache-2.0 as a base for derivation):
the IDENTIFIER rule, naming conventions (camelCase vs snake_case), grammar
scope, and overall structure differ substantially. The only shared constructs
are minimal, specification-mandated token forms (e.g. verbatim string syntax)
that represent the sole correct encoding of those C# language features and
therefore carry no independent copyright.
